TextChange: Of course marketing has always been with us. I  => I

We are bombarded every day by imagery, and quite a bit of it has been created in an effort to sell us something. Whether it be food, cars, or even more often these days health care medications and services. Many younger people may not realize this, but there once was a time when you didn't see these advertisements for prescription medications or hospital services. It wasn't even that long ago. When it comes to marketing these days, I feel as though American society has been like a frog slowly being boiled alive in a pot of water.
